a recollection at the Library

00:02:05.770 --> 00:02:09.560
of Congress, which is one of the
top collections in the world.

00:02:09.560 --> 00:02:16.350
And we often have many scholars,
researchers from all over the world

00:02:16.350 --> 00:02:20.150
who come to consult
these collections.

00:02:20.150 --> 00:02:25.110
And so this division -- I
always make a little commercial

00:02:25.110 --> 00:02:30.570
for our division, because our
division is the African Middle

00:02:30.570 --> 00:02:31.870
East Division.

00:02:31.870 --> 00:02:36.360
It is responsible for 78
countries around the world.

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:43.020
And our collections
are in the vernacular.

00:02:43.020 --> 00:02:47.430
They are housed, preserved in our
stacks, which are closed stacks,

00:02:47.430 --> 00:02:51.830
and which we use to
serve our patrons

00:02:51.830 --> 00:02:54.630
and our researchers as they come.

00:02:54.630 --> 00:02:58.840
These countries that
we're responsible for,

00:02:58.840 --> 00:03:01.490
or whose collections
we're responsible for,

00:03:01.490 --> 00:03:06.440
come from the whole continent of
Africa, north and Sub-Saharan.

00:03:06.440 --> 00:03:09.690
They come from the Middle East,

00:03:09.690 --> 00:03:14.350
including the Arab
world, Turkey and Iran.

00:03:14.350 --> 00:03:19.240
