00:12:55.350 --> 00:12:59.640
We're just focusing on
the exile experience.

00:12:59.640 --> 00:13:01.820
Why was I interested in this?

00:13:01.820 --> 00:13:03.120
Well, I think first of all,

00:13:03.120 --> 00:13:05.960
the exile experience is a
universal human condition.

00:13:05.960 --> 00:13:09.410
Throughout history, people
have been refugees forced

00:13:09.410 --> 00:13:10.960
from their countries.

00:13:10.960 --> 00:13:15.850
And today, as we know, this
is a very commonplace thing.

00:13:15.850 --> 00:13:22.050 position:56%
So I was very excited to look at
this through the eyes of one person,

00:13:22.050 --> 00:13:24.950
what was it like to be in exile?

00:13:24.950 --> 00:13:30.430 position:56%
Of course, as we know the background
to this, the emperor came to Britain

00:13:30.430 --> 00:13:36.580
